{"title_page": "National Union of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers and Coalmeters", "text_new": "{{Infobox Union\n|name= National Union of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers and Coalmeters\n|country= [[United Kingdom]]\n|affiliation=\n|members= 732 (1920)<ref name=\"eaton\">{{cite book|last1=Eaton|first1=Jack|last2=Gill|first2=Colin|title=The Trade Union Directory|date=1981|publisher=Pluto Press|location=London|isbn=0861043502|page=56}}</ref>\n|full_name= \n|native_name=\n|image= \n|founded= 1912\n|current=\n|head=\n|dissolved_date= 1 January 1922<ref name=\"eaton\" />\n|dissolved_state= Merged into\n|merged_into= [[Transport and General Workers' Union]]\n|people= G. N. Richmond, Secretary.\n|office= [[Plaistow, Newham]]\n|website=\n|footnotes=\n}}\n<!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->\n\nThe '''National Union of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers and Coalmeters''' was a [[trade union]] in the [[United Kingdom]].\n\nThe union was in existence by 1912, at which time it had branches in central London, [[Grays, Essex|Grays]], [[Millwall]], [[Southampton]], [[Surrey Docks]] and [[Tilbury]].  At the time, it was based in [[Plaistow, Newham|Plaistow]] and its secretary was G. N. Richmond.<ref name=\"smethurst\" />  Because of its location, it was also known as the \"East Ham Union\".<ref name=\"eaton\" />  It merged with the [[Transport and General Workers' Union]] in 1922.<ref name=\"smethurst\">John B. Smethurst and Peter Carter, ''Historical Directory of Trade Unions'', p.159</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of trade unions]]\n* [[Transport and General Workers' Union]]\n* [[TGWU amalgamations]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Portal|Organized labour}}\n\n{{Transport and General Workers' Union}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:National Union Of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers And Coalmeters}}\n[[Category:Defunct trade unions of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Port workers' trade unions]]\n[[Category:Transport and General Workers' Union amalgamations]]\n[[Category:Trade unions established in 1912]]\n[[Category:Trade unions disestablished in 1922]]\n[[Category:1912 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{UK-trade-union-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Union\n|name= National Union of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers and Coalmeters\n|country= [[United Kingdom]]\n|affiliation=\n|members= 732 (1920)<ref name=\"eaton\">{{cite book|last1=Eaton|first1=Jack|last2=Gill|first2=Colin|title=The Trade Union Directory|date=1981|publisher=Pluto Press|location=London|isbn=0861043502|page=56}}</ref>\n|full_name= \n|native_name=\n|image= \n|founded= 1912\n|current=\n|head=\n|dissolved_date= 1 January 1922<ref name=\"eaton\" />\n|dissolved_state= Merged into\n|merged_into= [[Transport and General Workers' Union]]\n|people= G. N. Richmond, Secretary.\n|office= [[Plaistow, Newham]]\n|website=\n|footnotes=\n}}\n<!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->\n\nThe '''National Union of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers and Coalmeters''' was a [[trade union]] in the [[United Kingdom]].\n\nThe union was in existence by 1912, at which time it had branches in central London, [[Grays]], [[Millwall]], [[Southampton]], [[Surrey Docks]] and [[Tilbury]].  At the time, it was based in [[Plaistow, Newham|Plaistow]] and its secretary was G. N. Richmond.<ref name=\"smethurst\" />  Because of its location, it was also known as the \"East Ham Union\".<ref name=\"eaton\" />  It merged with the [[Transport and General Workers' Union]] in 1922.<ref name=\"smethurst\">John B. Smethurst and Peter Carter, ''Historical Directory of Trade Unions'', p.159</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of trade unions]]\n* [[Transport and General Workers' Union]]\n* [[TGWU amalgamations]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{Portal|Organized labour}}\n\n{{Transport and General Workers' Union}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:National Union Of Ships' Clerks, Grain Weighers And Coalmeters}}\n[[Category:Defunct trade unions of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Port workers' trade unions]]\n[[Category:Transport and General Workers' Union amalgamations]]\n[[Category:Trade unions established in 1912]]\n[[Category:Trade unions disestablished in 1922]]\n[[Category:1912 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n\n\n{{UK-trade-union-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Crouch, Swale", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toGrays(link changed toGrays, Essex) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Union_of_Ships%27_Clerks,_Grain_Weighers_and_Coalmeters"}
{"title_page": "Hinjawadi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Hinjawadi (Phase-I, II & III)\n| other_name                      = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Pune Metropolitan Region]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| nickname                        = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18.594596|N|73.718519|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_type3               = [[Talukas in Pune district|Taluka]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Maharashtra]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Pune district|Pune]]\n| subdivision_name3               = [[Mulshi taluka|Mulshi]]\n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| founder                         = \n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = [[[http://www.pmrda.gov.in/ PMRDA]]]\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = \n| area_rank                       = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| population_total                = \n| population_as_of                = \n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_rank                 = \n| population_demonym              = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = [[Postal Index Number|PIN]]\n| postal_code                     = 411057\n| area_code                       = 91-(0)-20\n| area_code_type                  = Telephone code\n| registration_plate              = MH-14\n| blank1_name_sec1                = \n| blank1_info_sec1                = \n| blank1_name_sec2                = \n| blank1_info_sec2                = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| demographics1_info1             = [[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n[[File:India Technology.jpg|thumb|[[Infosys]], Hinjawadi Phase-2]]\n[[File:Embassy TechZone.jpg|thumb|[[Embassy Tech Zone]], Hinjawadi Phase-2]]\n| official_name                   = \n| native_name                     = Hinjawadi\n}}\n\n{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n\n'''Hinjawadi is''' located in South-Western part of the city of Pune, India.\n\n==History==\nPreviously Hinjawadi was a village until the construction of the Rajiv Gandhi Infotech Park. Now it is one of the epicentre of IT industry in Pune. To improve the overall planning and development of Hinjewadi area, it was brought under the jurisdiction of PMRDA. The state government in the past rejected the demands to bring the area under the jurisdiction of either PMC or PCMC as the area needed special attentionThe park comprises three phases with further phases planned. Hinjawadi Industries Association (HIA) was laid out to provide a joint forum to all stakeholders based out of Hinjawadi and nearby places.\n\nHinjawadi is a proposed hub for integrated townships in Pimpri-Chinchwad.<ref name=\"moneycontrol\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moneycontrol.com/news/real-estate/integrated-townshipspune_865368.html|title=Integrated townships in Pune&nbsp;\u2014 Moneycontrol.com|publisher=moneycontrol.com|accessdate=2014-01-30}}</ref> The new ''Special Township Policy Act'' of the Maharashtra government has laid down an integrated approach to development of townships to de-congest [[Pune Municipal Corporation]] areas and encourage new settlements in its periphery though higher FSI (floor space index) than what is normally allowed in the municipal limits.\n\n== Transport ==\n\n===Road transport===\nDue to rapid development, Hinjawadi is facing serious traffic problems during peak hours. From 8.00&nbsp;AM to 12:00&nbsp;PM and 5.30 PM to 8.00 PM, HMVs (Heavy Motor Vehicles) are not allowed to enter the area due to high congestion on the roads and the number of vehicles are increasing due to a lot of career opportunities. Above 2.5 Lacs employees travel daily to and from the IT park.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/pune-news/commuters-heave-a-sigh-of-relief-after-one-way-traffic-eases-congestion-in-hinjewadi/story-7rGoia9jvtAzTfR6Ssvy7M.html|title=Commuters heave a sigh of relief after one-way traffic eases congestion in Hinjewadi}}</ref>\n\nIn Rainy seasons people starting from Phase 3 or Phase 2 used to spend minimum 1 hour in just crossing Hinjawadi and to reach till Wakad bridge which is merely 3 Kilometer distance.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nThe roads are potholes laden and full of encroachments. The Hinjawadi Industries Association (HIA) had logged numerous complaints to the local and state government,{{cn|date=March 2020}} but nothing has moved. The employees of IT companies also protested by forming a human chain,{{cn|date=March 2020}} but it has made no impact on the authorities. As this was not enough, the small lanes within the IT park were dug up for pipeline work{{cn|date=March 2020}} and then never reconstructed. Because of the worst road conditions, minor accidents involving IT employees is a regular picture.{{cn|date=March 2020}} Back, Neck and Shoulder injuries are common among the engineers.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nThere are two more approach roads proposed to reduce the traffic congestion, but almost after 15 years of establishment of the IT park, these roads still remain proposed. The Wakad bridge is a planning marvel in itself. When the authorities were planning for Phase 1 till Phase 4 of the IT park, this bridge was constructed with only 2 lanes. So from both sides, 3 lanes merge into single lane, creating traffic mess day and night.\n\n===Hinjawadi Line-3 Pune Metro Railways===\n\nHinjawadi Metro [[Line 3 (Pune Metro)]] is under construction. And it is inaugurated by India Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]]\n\nHinjawadi Metro Railway: [[Line 3 (Pune Metro)]] Stations\u2013 Megapolis Circle (Including Bhoirwadi), Quadron, Dohler, Infosys Phase II, Wipro Phase II, Pall India, Shivaji Chowk, Hinjawadi, Wakad Chowk, Balewadi Stadium, NICMAR, Ram Nagar, Laxmi Nagar, Balewadi Phata, Baner Gaon, Baner, Krushi Anusadhan, Sakal Nagar, University, R.B.I., Agriculture College and Shivaji Nagar (interchange with Line-1). Mahatoba temple is located on a hill in Hinjawadi.\n\n==Education==\n#[[International Institute of Information Technology,Pune]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.isquareit.edu.in}}</ref> Hinjawadi  \n#[[Symbiosis International University]], Hinjawadi\n# Alard Group of Institutes, Hinjawadi\n# Alard Public School, Hinjawadi\n# Alard College of Engineering and Management, Hinjawadi\n# Alard College of Pharmacy, Hinjawadi\n# Alard Institute Of Management Sciences, Hinjawadi\n# International Institute Of Management Studies, Nere\n#[[Mercedes-Benz International School]], Hinjawadi\n#Blue Ridge Public School,<ref name=\"brps\">{{Citation|last=|first=|title=Blue Ridge Public School|url=http://blueridgepublicschool.com/|volume=|page=|pages=|year=|publication-place=|publisher=Blue Ridge Public School|accessdate=26 February 2017}}</ref> Hinjawadi\n#[[Pawar Public School]],<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title=Pawar Public School |publisher=Pawar Public School |publication-place= |page= |url=http://www.ppshinjewadi.com/ |accessdate=26 February 2017 }}</ref> Maan\n#[[VIBGYOR High School]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vibgyorhigh.com/pune-hinjewedi.php|title=VIBGYOR HIGH Hinjawadi}}{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Hinjawadi\n#Mount Litera Zee School, Hinjawadi \n#SPORTSLIFE Football School,<ref>{{Citation |last= |first= |year= |title= SPORTSLIFE Football School |publisher=SPORTSLIFE Football School |publication-place= |page= |url=http://www.sportslife.co.in/|accessdate=26 February 2017 }}</ref>{{failed verification|date=December 2017}} Hinjawadi\n\n==Geography==\n{{Geographic Location\n|title     = '''Hinjawadi'''\n|North     = [[Marunji]]\n|East      = [[Wakad]]\n|Centre    = Hinjawadi\n|West      = [[Maan, Pune|Maan]]\n|South     = [[Mahalunge]]\n}}\n\nHinjawadi is mainly classified in three zones,\n\n* Phase 1 \n* Phase 2 \n* Phase 3\n\n==See also==\n*[[Magarpatta]]\n*[[Kharadi]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Suburbs of Pune}}\n\n[[Category:High-technology business districts in India]]\n[[Category:Economy of Pune]]\n[[Category:Neighbourhoods in Pune]]\n[[Category:Software technology parks in Pune]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Hinjawadi (Phase-I, II & III)\n| other_name                      = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Pune Metropolitan Region]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| nickname                        = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Maharashtra\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Maharashtra, India\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|18.594596|N|73.718519|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name         