ndustantimes.com/pune-news/commuters-heave-a-sigh-of-relief-after-one-way-traffic-eases-congestion-in-hinjewadi/story-7rGoia9jvtAzTfR6Ssvy7M.html|title=Commuters heave a sigh of relief after one-way traffic eases congestion in Hinjewadi}}</ref>\n\nIn Rainy seasons people starting from Phase 3 or Phase 2 used to spend minimum 1 hour in just crossing Hinjawadi and to reach till Wakad bridge which is merely 3 Kilometer distance.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nThe roads are potholes laden and full of encroachments. The Hinjawadi Industries Association (HIA) had logged numerous complaints to the local and state government,{{cn|date=March 2020}} but nothing has moved. The employees of IT companies also protested by forming a human chain,{{cn|date=March 2020}} but it has made no impact on the authorities. As this was not enough, the small lanes within the IT park were dug up for pipeline work{{cn|date=March 2020}} and then never reconstructed. Because of the worst road conditions, minor accidents involving IT employees is a regular picture.{{cn|date=March 2020}} Back, Neck and Shoulder injuries are common among the engineers.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nThere are two more approach roads proposed to reduce the traffic congestion, but almost after 15 years of establishment of the IT park, these roads still remain proposed. The Wakad bridge is a planning marvel in itself. When the authorities were planning for Phase 1 till Phase 4 of the IT park, this bridge was constructed with only 2 lanes. So from both sides, 3 lanes merge into single lane, creating traffic mess day and night.\n\n===Hinjawadi Line-3 Pune Metro Railways===\n\nHinjawadi Metro [[Line 3 (Pune Metro)]] is under construction. And it is inaugurated by India Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]]\n\nHinjawadi Metro Railway: [[Line 3 (Pune Metro)]] Stations\u2013 Megapolis Circle (Including Bhoirwadi), Quadron, Dohler, Infosys Phase II, Wipro Phase II, Pall India, Shivaji Chowk, Hinjawadi, Wakad Chowk, Balewadi Stadium, NICMAR, R