stic test, able to detect COVID-19 in just 45 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cepheid.mediaroom.com/2020-03-21-Cepheid-Receives-Emergency-Use-Authorization-from-FDA-for-Rapid-SARS-CoV-2-Test|title=Cepheid Receives Emergency Use Authorization from FDA for Rapid SARS-CoV-2 Test|website=Cepheid|date=March 21, 2020|access-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/21/politics/fda-coronavirus-test/index.html|title=FDA authorizes new test that could detect coronavirus in about 45 minutes|website=CNN|date=March 21, 2020|access-date=March 21, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 22]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic\n***President Trump says the [[United States National Guard|National Guard]] has been activated in California, Washington, and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]], thus far the most impacted states during the pandemic.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/trump-says-he-s-activated-national-guard-new-york-california-n1166211|title=Trump says he's activated National Guard in New York, California and Washington state|work=NBC News|date=22 March 2020|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Washington National Guard]] clarifies that it was yet to be \"activated\", only declared available if needed.<ref>{{cite news|title=WA National Guard says it\u2019s not activated yet, despite Pres. Trump announcement|url=https://www.kiro7.com/news/local/wa-national-guard-says-its-not-activated-yet-despite-pres-trump-announcement/YKK2RABFS5FU3PBWPWEYY3NAZE/|work=KIRO 7|date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n***The [[USNS Comfort (T-AH-20)|USNS ''Comfort'' (T-AH-20)]] [[hospital ship]] is announced to be deployed to New York. The [[USNS Mercy (T-AH-19)|USNS ''Mercy'' (T-AH-19)]] is to be deployed to Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://nypost.com/2020/03/22/navy-hospital-ship-will-be-sent-to-new-york-to-help-battle-coronavirus/|title=Navy hospital ship will be sent to New York to help battle coronavirus|date=22 March 2020|work