 a [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]] hospital believed to be treating COVID-19 patients.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/domestic-terrorist-allegedly-plotted-car-bomb-hospital-coronavirus/story?id=69803480|title=Domestic terror suspect allegedly plotted to use car bomb on hospital during coronavirus pandemic|work=ABC News|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n**A [[Gallup (company)|Gallup]] poll places President Trump's approval rating at 49 percent, his highest thus far.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/489285-gallup-trump-job-approval-rating-matches-all-time-high|work=The Hill|date=24 March 2020|title=Gallup: Trump job approval rating matches all-time high}}</ref> A separate [[The Hill (newspaper)|''Hill'']]-[[Harris Insights & Analytics|HarrisX]] poll places him at 50 percent, his highest since August [[2018 in the United States|2018]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/hilltv/what-americas-thinking/489340-poll-trump-lands-50-percent-approval-for-first-time-in-two|title=Poll: Trump approval rating hits 50 percent for first time in almost 2 years|work=The Hill|date=24 March 2020|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 25]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic: \n***Deaths from COVID-19 in the U.S. surpass 1,000 as the total number of cases reaches almost 69,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/26/coronavirus-live-updates-china-cases-spains-death-count-surpasses-china.html|title=Coronavirus live updates: US deaths soar past 1,000, according to Johns Hopkins University|website=CNBC|date=March 25, 2020|access-date=March 26, 2020}}</ref>\n***The White House and the Senate agree to a [[Coronavirus Aid, Relief, and Economic Security Act|$2 trillion stimulus package]]&ndash;the largest in U.S. history&ndash;to [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States#Economic impact|boost the economy]] amid the ongoing pandemic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/25/politics/stimulus-senate-action-coronavirus/index.html|title=White House, Senate reach historic $2 trillion stimulus deal amid growing coronavirus fears|website=CNN|date=March 25, 2020|access-date=March 25, 2020}}</ref> The Senate subsequently approves the negotiated bill (the CARES Act) in a 96\u20130 vote.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Pramuk |first1=Jacob |title=Senate passes $2 trillion coronavirus stimulus package, sending it to the House |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/25/senate-passes-2-trillion-coronavirus-stimulus-package.html |website=CNBC |accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref> Trump signs the bill into law on March 27 after a House [[Voice vote#United States|voice vote]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/27/house-passes-2-trillion-coronavirus-stimulus-bill-sends-it-to-trump.html|work=CNBC|date=27 March 2020|title=Trump signs $2 trillion coronavirus relief bill as the US tries to prevent economic devastation}}</ref>\n***[[The Pentagon]] orders a 60-day halt on all overseas troop travel and movement as 227 U.S. troops have thus far tested positive for COVID-19. The withdrawal from Afghanistan will continue.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pentagon orders halt overseas movement for U.S. military over coronavirus|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020|work=Reuters|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200325203242-zgoc4}}</ref>\n*[[March 26]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic: \n***The number of COVID-19 infections exceeds 82,000 &ndash; surpassing the numbers in China and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|Italy]] &ndash; as the U.S. now has more cases reported than any other country to date.<ref>{{cite news|title=Coronavirus US live: US now has more cases than any other country \u2013 as it happened|date=27 March 2020|accessdate=27 March 2020|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2020/mar/26/coronavirus-us-live-house-vote-2tn-stimulus-package-bill-senate-news-updates-trump}}</ref>\n***The Department of Labor reports that 3.28 million Americans filed for [[unemployment benefits]] in the last week, the largest increase in U.S. history. It supersedes the all-time high of 695,000 in October [[1982 in the United States|1982]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/26/weekly-jobless-claims.html|title=Jobless claims soar past 3 million to record as coronavirus sends Americans to the unemployment line|date=26 March 2020|work=CNBC}}</ref>\n**The Trump administration indicts Venezuelan President [[Nicol\u00e1s Maduro]]'s government of [[Illegal drug trade|drug trafficking]] and [[narcoterrorism]] and offers a $15 million reward for information leading to his arrest.<ref>[https://www.infobae.com/america/venezuela/2020/03/26/estados-unidos-sancionara-al-regimen-de-nicolas-maduro-por-sus-vinculos-con-el-narcoterrorismo-internacional/ The United States accused Nicol\u00e1s Maduro of narco-terrorism and offered USD 15 million for data leading to his arrest] {{in lang|es}} Infobae, 26 Mar 2020</ref>\n**The [[United States Space Force|Space Force]] launches its first satellite, an [[Advanced Extremely High Frequency|Advanced Extremely High Frequency (AEHF-6)]] military communications satellite that cost $1.4 billion.<ref>[https://www.space.com/why-space-force-launching-rockets-coronavirus-pandemic.html Here's why the Space Force just launched a rocket as the world fights the coronavirus pandemic] By Mike Wall, Space.com, 27 March 2020</ref>\n*[[March 29]] \u2013 As part of a [[Withdrawal of U.S. troops from Iraq (2020)|withdrawal effort]], U.S.-led coalition troops pull out of [[K-1 Air Base]] in Iraq, the third site left by coalition forces this month. At least $1.1 million of equipment are transferred to the Iraqis.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/us-led-coalition-pulls-3rd-113811539.html US-led forces pull out of 3rd Iraqi base this month] by SAMYA KULLAB, AP, 29 Mar 2020</ref>\n*[[March 31]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic:\n*** There are more than 163,000 reported COVID-19 cases thus far as the national death toll reaches 3,000. Three-quarters of the U.S. population are under lockdown as [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Maryland|Maryland]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Virginia|Virginia]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Arizona|Arizona]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Tennessee |Tennessee]] become the latest states to restrict movement.<ref>{{cite news|title=Coronavirus: Three out of four Americans under some form of lockdown|date=31 March 2020|accessdate=31 March 2020|work=BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-52103066}}</ref>\n***U.S. dairy producers dump milk as farmers cannot get their product to market because of a truck driver shortage.<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-dairy-insight/u-s-dairy-farmers-dump-milk-as-pandemic-upends-food-markets-idUSKBN21L1DW U.S. dairy farmers dump milk as pandemic upends food markets] Reuters, 3 Apr 2020</ref>\n**The [[Federal Communications Commission]] mandates cell phone providers implement [[STIR/SHAKEN]] by June 30, 2021 for large carriers and June 30, 2022 for small carriers to prevent [[robocall]]s maliciously using [[caller ID spoofing]] to avoid being traced.<ref>[https://techcrunch.com/2020/03/31/fcc-mandates-strict-caller-id-authentication-to-beat-back-robocalls/ FCC mandates strict caller ID authentication to beat back robocalls] Tech Crunch, March 31, 2020</ref>\n**A 6.5{{M|?}} [[2020 Central Idaho earthquake|earthquake]] strikes [[Central Idaho]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.heraldmailmedia.com/news/nation/days-after-idaho-s-earthquake-experts-seek-answers-about-historic-unexpected-event/article_ccd3b483-f528-55ca-8c27-d2eba918084d.html|accessdate=April 10, 2020|date=April 9, 2020|title=Days after Idaho\u2019s earthquake, experts seek answers about historic, unexpected event|work=Herald Mail Media}}</ref>\n\n===April===\n*[[April 1]]\n**The Trump administration deploys anti-drug Navy ships and [[Airborne early warning and control|AWACS]] planes near [[United States\u2013Venezuela relations|Venezuela]] 