d-cruise-ship-japan-test-positive/story?id=69026322}}</ref>\n**The national [[Boy Scouts of America]] files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy. Independently funded local councils are not effected.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/boy-scouts-america-hobbled-multiple-sex-abuse-lawsuits-declares-bankruptcy-n1125026?cid=sm_npd_nn_fb_ma Boy Scouts of America, hobbled by multiple sex-abuse lawsuits, files for bankruptcy protection] NBC News, February 18, 2020</ref>\n**[[Pier 1 Imports]] files for Chapter 11 bankruptcy and plans to do so in [[Canada]] as well.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/sergeiklebnikov/2020/02/17/pier-1-is-officially-for-sale-after-filing-for-chapter-11-bankruptcy/ Pier 1 Is Officially For Sale After Filing For Chapter 11 Bankruptcy] by Sergei Klebnikov, Forbes, February 17, 2020</ref>\n**[[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] CEO [[Jeff Bezos]] pledges $10 billion to fight [[climate change]] using a new fund called the [[Bezos Earth Fund]].<ref>[https://www.foxnews.com/science/jeff-bezos-donates-10b-to-fight-climate-change Jeff Bezos donates $10B to fight climate change] By Chris Ciaccia, Fox News, February 17, 2020</ref>\n*[[February 19]] &ndash; The [[Utah State Senate|Utah Senate]] votes to decriminalize [[polygamy]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Utah Senate supports bill decriminalising polygamy |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-51562737 |accessdate=February 19, 2020|work=BBC News |date=February 19, 2020 }}</ref>\n*[[February 20]] &ndash; [[Political consulting|Political consultant]] [[Roger Stone]] is sentenced to 40 months in prison after being found guilty of witness tampering, obstructing an official proceeding, and five counts of making false statements.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/latest-roger-stone-remain-free-pending-sentencing-67044838 |title=The Latest: Roger Stone to remain free pending sentencing |agency=The Associated Press |work=[[ABC News]] |date=November 15, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[February 21]] &ndash; [[Wells