rch 5, 2020 }}</ref>\n**Senator [[Elizabeth Warren]] suspends her [[Elizabeth_Warren_2020_presidential_campaign|presidential campaign]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Elizabeth Warren ends presidential bid|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51759386|publisher=BBC News|date=March 5, 2020 |accessdate=March 5, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 6]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic\n***[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Florida|Florida]] reports two deaths from COVID-19, the first confirmed U.S. fatalities outside of the [[West Coast of the United States|west coast]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Florida reports its first 2 coronavirus deaths |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/07/us/florida-coronavirus-deaths/index.html|publisher=CNN|date=March 7, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n***The annual [[South by Southwest]] (SXSW) festival is [[South by Southwest#2020 cancellation|canceled]] due to COVID-19 fears; it is the first time the event has been canceled in its 34-year history.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/6/21162247/sxsw-2020-cancelled-coronavirus-austin-texas-virus-fears-public-health-event|work=The Verge|date=March 6, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020|title=SXSW 2020 canceled due to coronavirus}}</ref>\n**President Trump announces Representative [[Mark_Meadows_(North_Carolina_politician)|Mark Meadows]] will succeed [[Mick Mulvaney]] as [[White House Chief of Staff]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Trump replaces Mick Mulvaney with Mark Meadows as chief of staff |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/06/politics/trump-mulvaney-out/index.html|publisher=CNN|date=March 7, 2020|accessdate=March 7, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 7]] &ndash; COVID-19 pandemic: [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C.]] records its first case of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web |title=Washington, D.C., has first 'presumptive positive' test for coronavirus|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-washingtondc/washington-d-c-has-first-presumptive-positive-test-for-coronavirus-idUSKBN20U0ZY|publisher=Reuters|date=March 7, 2020 |accessdate=March 8, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[March 9]]\n**[[2020 stock market crash#Black Monday (9 March)|Black Monday 2020]]: Share prices fall sharply, in response to economic concerns and the impact of COVID-19. The Dow Jones industrial average plunges more than 2,000 points, its biggest ever fall in intraday trading.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51796806|title=Black Monday: Shares face biggest fall since financial crisis|website=BBC News|language=en|date=March 9, 2020|access-date=March 9, 2020}}</ref> [[Oil prices]] plunge by as much as 30% in early trading, the biggest fall since 1991, after Saudi Arabia launches a [[2020 Russia\u2013Saudi Arabia oil price war|price war]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Oil prices plunge as much as 30% after OPEC deal failure sparks price war |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/08/oil-plummets-30percent-as-opec-deal-failure-sparks-price-war-fears.html |accessdate=March 9, 2020 |agency=CNBC}}</ref>\n**The U.S. begins a conditional [[Withdrawal of U.S. troops from Afghanistan#Plans by the administration of Donald Trump|troop withdrawal]] from [[Afghanistan]]; American troop numbers are to be reduced from 12,000 to 8,600 within 135 days.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-51810498|work=BBC|title=Afghanistan conflict: US begins withdrawing troops|date=March 9, 2020|accessdate=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[March 10]] &ndash; COVID-19 pandemic: The number of COVID-19 cases in the United States exceeds 1,000, with a 50% increase within a 24-hour period and infections reported in 35 states.<ref>{{cite web |title=US coronavirus cases pass 1,000 as crisis hits the campaign trail|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/11/us-coronavirus-cases-pass-1000-as-crisis-hits-the-campaign-trail|publisher=The Guardian|date=March 11, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[March 11]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic: President Trump announces a [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States#Travel and entry restrictions|30-day ban]] on incoming travel from [[Europe]] (with the exception of the [[United Kingdom]]), effective midnight EDT (0400 GMT) on March 13. The announcement occurs the same day the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) declares the COVID-19 outbreak a [[pandemic]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51857462 |title=Coronavirus: EU condemns Trump travel ban on 26 European countries|work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=March 12, 2020 |accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref> The travel ban is extended to the UK and [[Ireland]] on March 16.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51891662 |title=Coronavirus: US to extend travel ban to UK and Ireland |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n**Persian Gulf crisis: Two Americans and one British soldier are killed in a [[2020 Camp Taji attack|rocket attack]] in [[Taji, Iraq]].\n**The Justice Department and the [[Drug Enforcement Administration]] announce the arrest of more than 600 alleged members of the [[Jalisco New Generation Cartel]].<ref>[https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/487064-feds-arrests-over-600-alleged-mexican-cartel-members Feds arrest over 600 alleged Mexican cartel members] {{in lang|en}} BY J. EDWARD MORENO, The Hill, March 11, 2020</ref>\n**Former film producer [[Harvey Weinstein]] is sentenced to 23 years in prison for rape and sexual assault.<ref>{{cite web |title=Harvey Weinstein jailed for 23 years in rape trial\n|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-51840532|publisher=BBC News|date=March 11, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 12]]\n**[[2020 stock market crash#Black Thursday (12 March)|Black Thursday 2020]]: Following a series of recent major falls, the Dow Jones plunges yet again, this time by over 9.5%, along with markets around the world.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51829852 |title=Coronavirus: Global stocks plunge as coronavirus fears spread |work=BBC News |publisher=BBC |date=March 12, 2020 |accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n**A federal judge orders [[whistleblower]] [[Chelsea Manning]] be released from prison, but must pay accrued fines of $256,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/12/politics/chelsea-manning-suicide-attempt-virginia-jail/index.html|title=Federal judge orders Chelsea Manning's release from jail|author1=Katelyn Polantz |author2=Veronica Stracqualursi |author3=Mark Morales|website=CNN|date=March 12, 2020|access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 13]]\n**COVID-19 pandemic\n***President Trump declares a [[List_of_national_emergencies_in_the_United_States|national emergency]] in response to the COVID-19 pandemic, freeing up $50 billion in disaster relief funds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2020/mar/13/donald-trump-coronavirus-national-emergency-sketch|title='I don't take responsibility': Trump shakes hands and spreads blame over coronavirus|website=The Guardian|date=March 14, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n***The [[Food and Drug Administration]] (FDA) grants emergency authorization for a coronavirus test by Swiss diagnostics maker [[Hoffmann-La_Roche|Roche]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.roche.com/media/releases/med-cor-2020-03-13.htm|title=Roche's cobas SARS-CoV-2 Test to detect novel coronavirus receives FDA Emergency Use Authorization and is available in markets accepting the CE mark|date=March 13, 2020|access-date=March 13, 2020|work=Roche}}</ref>\n**[[Bill Gates]] steps down from the board of [[Microsoft]] to focus on philanthropic activities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-51883377|title=Bill Gates steps down from Microsoft board to focus on philanthropy|website=BBC News|date=March 13, 2020|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n*[[March 15]] &ndash; COVID-19 pandemic: The [[Federal Reserve]] announces that it will cut its target interest rate to 0 to 0.25 percent.<ref>{{