a|for the first time ever]].<ref>{{cite news|work=The Guardian|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2020/mar/24/us-box-office-zero-revenue-first-time-ever-coronavirus-the-invisible-man|title=US box office records zero takings for first time ever as coronavirus crisis bites|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n***[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Nevada|Nevada]] governor [[Steve Sisolak]] bans the use of anti-[[malaria]] drugs for COVID-19 treatment, notably [[chloroquine]] and [[hydroxychloroquine]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2020/mar/24/sisolak-bars-malaria-drugs-for-coronavirus-patient/|title=Sisolak bars malaria drugs for coronavirus patients|work=Las Vegas Sun|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n***FBI agents kill a man in [[Belton, Missouri]] suspected of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Missouri#Timeline|plotting a bombing attack]] at a [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]] hospital believed to be treating COVID-19 patients.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/domestic-terrorist-allegedly-plotted-car-bomb-hospital-coronavirus/story?id=69803480|title=Domestic terror suspect allegedly plotted to use car bomb on hospital during coronavirus pandemic|work=ABC News|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n**A [[Gallup (company)|Gallup]] poll places President Trump's approval rating at 49 percent, his highest thus far.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/489285-gallup-trump-job-approval-rating-matches-all-time-high|work=The Hill|date=24 March 2020|title=Gallup: Trump job approval rating matches all-time high}}</ref> A separate [[The Hill (newspaper)|''Hill'']]-[[Harris Insights & Analytics|HarrisX]] poll places him at 50 percent, his highest since August [[2018 in the United States|2018]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://thehill.com/hilltv/what-americas-thinking/489340-poll-trump-lands-50-percent-approval-for-first-time-in-two|title=Poll: Trump approval rating hits 50 percent for first time in almost 2 years|work=T