uck dies after serving in Georgia House for nearly 4 decades]</ref>\n** [[Lorraine Chandler]], soul singer and songwriter (b. [[1946]])<ref>[http://www.soulandjazzandfunk.com/news/6690-lorraine-chandler-dies.html Lorraine Chandler Dies...]</ref>\n** [[R. Kern Eutsler]], United Methodist bishop (b. [[1919]])<ref>[https://www.unitedmethodistbishops.org/newsdetail/bishop-r-kern-eutsler-dies-at-100-13134579 Bishop R. Kern Eutsler dies at 100]</ref>\n** [[Nick Fish]], politician and lawyer (b. [[1958]])<ref>[https://www.oregonlive.com/portland/2020/01/portland-commissioner-nick-fish-dies-of-cancer.html Portland Commissioner Nick Fish dies of cancer]</ref>\n** [[Sam Wyche]], football player and coach (b. [[1945]])<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/nfl/bengals/2020/01/02/sam-wyche-dies-cincinnati-bengals-coach/2798007001/ Former Cincinnati Bengals coach Sam Wyche dies at 74]</ref>\n* [[January 3]] \n** [[Ken Fuson]], journalist (b. [[1956]])<ref>[https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/2020/01/03/register-iowa-storyteller-journalist-reporter-ken-fuson-dies-63/2805696001/ 'An extraordinarily gifted storyteller': Former Register writer Ken Fuson dies at 63]</ref>\n** [[Reuben Hersh]], mathematician (b. [[1927]])<ref>[https://math.unm.edu/news-events/news/reuben-hersh-passed-away Reuben Hersh passed away]</ref>\n* [[January 4]] \n** [[Emanuel Borok]], violinist and concertmaster (b. [[1944]])<ref>[https://www.dallasnews.com/arts-entertainment/performing-arts/2020/01/06/emanuel-borok-longtime-dallas-symphony-concertmaster-has-died-after-battling-lung-cancer/ Emanuel Borok, longtime Dallas Symphony concertmaster, has died after battling lung cancer]</ref>\n** [[James Parks Morton]], Episcopal priest (b. [[1930]])<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/07/nyregion/james-morton-dead.html James Parks Morton, Dean Who Brought a Cathedral to Life, Dies at 89]</ref>\n* [[January 5]] \u2013 [[Betty Pat Gatliff]], forensic artist (b. [[1930]])<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2