n|}\n\n==Civilian Service ==\n\n<br />\n\n[[File:General William J. Walker.jpg|thumb|Special Agent William J Walker, DEA, Retired, bio photo]]\nWalker is the former Vice Chairman, Board of Directors of the [[Young Marines]], a military affiliated non-profit service organization for boys and girls ages eight through high school that provides developmental programs that nurtures and encourages its over 10,000 members into becoming responsible citizens who enjoy a positive and drug-free lifestyle. Walker is a member of [[Alpha Phi Alpha]] and [[Sigma Pi Phi]] fraternities.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nWalker concurrently serves as the Director of the District of Columbia National Guard and is a member of the Headquarters Department of the Army Senior Executive Service.\n==References==\n{{reflist}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dc.ng.mil/About-Us/State-Partnership-Program/|title=DCNG Partnership Program|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n<references /><br /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dc.ng.mil/Components/|title=The District of Columbia National Guard|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>{{Authority control}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dcmilitary.com/dc_military_mag/features/dcng-celebrates--year-history-of-the-u-s-army/article_d64a600b-09f6-5e2b-85eb-81981e50c04f.html|title=WO's 100-year celebration|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Walker, William J.}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:University of Illinois at Chicago alumni]]\n[[Category:Chicago State University alumni]]\n[[Category:National Intelligence University alumni]]\n[[Category:American University alumni]]\n[[Category:Military personnel from Richmond, Virginia]]\n[[Category:American army personnel of the War in Afghanistan (2001\u2013present)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of th